Here are the classes, structs, unions and interfaces with brief descriptions:
CMLAddDataPubParamsThis class wraps the parameters used notify the Ambassador which data classes this federate will publish
CMLAddDataPubResponseClass wrapper for Ambassador's response to a request to add data publications
CMLAddDataSubParamsThis class wraps the parameters used notify the Ambassador which data classes this federate will subscribe to
CMLAddDataSubResponseClass wrapper for Ambassador's response to a request to add data subscriptions
CMLAircraftArrivalDataClass CMLAircraftArrivalData events should be generated when an aircraft arrives at its destination. The actual definition of arrival is left up to the initiator of the event but is generally held to be when the aircraft has touched its wheels on the runway
CMLAircraftDepartureDataClass CMLAircraftDepartureData events should be generated when the aircraft departs from the airport. The actual definition for departure is left up to the initiator of the event but is generally held to be when the wheels leave the runway and the plane moves into local control
CMLAircraftTaxiInClass CMLAircraftTaxiIn class events are generated when an aircraft leaves the gate to begin taxiing out for departure
CMLAircraftTaxiOutClass CMLAircraftTaxiOut class events are generated when an aircraft leaves the gate to begin taxiing out for departure
CMLAmbassadorClass used to manage requests from the client application
CMLDataEventThis class wraps the information associated with a data event
CMLDataObjectBase class from which all Muthur data classes are derived
CMLDataStreamClass used to serialize CMLDataObject derived classes
CMLEventBase class for all derived Ambassador response classes
CMLExceptionClass used to pass information to the client when errors occur
CMLFedExecModelClass wrapper for an individual Federation Execution Model (FEM)
CMLFlightPlanFiledClass CMLFlightPlanFiled class objects are used to update the flight plans or routes of a current aircraft that match the key attributes
CMLFlightPositionClass CMLFlightPosition class objects provide an update on the flight position of a previously spawned aircraft whether in the air or on the ground. In order to ensure that the updates can be applied to the current aircraft the appropriate key attributes such as acid and tailNumber need to match the corresponding current active aircraft. This matching of key attributes applies to all updates against current aircraft
CMLHandleBase class for all derived Ambassador response classes
CMLHelperClass wrapper for set of static helper functions
CMLJoinFedParamsClass wrapper for parameters used to join a federation
CMLJoinFedResponseThis class wraps the Ambassador's response to a JoinFed request
CMLKillAircraftClass CMLKillAircraft objects are created when a user deletes or removes an aircraft. The attributes are either the unique ID taken from the particular object or a match on the aircraft tail number. Since these are key attributes of the object no additional attributes are required
CMLListFEMParamsClass wrapper for parameters used to get the list of Federation Execution Models from the Ambassador
CMLListFEMResponseClass wrapper for the Ambassador's response to a ListFedExecModels request
